  "source": "openstax-chemistry-2e",
  "conditions": [
    "The signature is one reactant giving two or more products.",
    "An energy input (heat, light, or electricity) usually drives it — but this Atlas describes the change, not how to carry it out."
  ],
  "misconceptions": [
    {
      "claim": "Decomposition always means a redox reaction.",
      "refute": "Not always. When a carbonate splits into a metal oxide and carbon dioxide, no element goes free — every atom keeps its oxidation state. Releasing a free element (O2, H2) is what makes the other examples redox."
    }
  ],
